  "title": "Site Engineer [Utility]/ New Viaduct proj/ $7.5K Basic+Vb/ A1 maincon/ 5days/ West  area",
  "description": "<ul><li><strong>Upto $7.5K basic + Bonus</strong></li><li><strong>Permanent position.</strong></li><li><strong>New Viaduct project @ West area.</strong></li><li><strong>2 vacancies available.</strong></li><li><strong>MNC & Leading A1 Main contractor!</strong></li><li><strong>Having utility diversion experience is mandatory. </strong></li></ul><p><strong>Job Description:</strong></p><ul><li>Involving in site utilities diversion work.</li><li>Coordination the utilities diversion route, supporting structure.</li><li>Manage utility construction projects, developing project scope, timelines, specifications, and budgets</li><li>Identify and resolve system failures and perform on oversee preventative maintenance</li><li>Monitoring system efficiency, energy and material usage.</li><li>Compile data on utility process units.</li><li>Direct project groups and/or technicians, providing guidance on utility process, design, and construction</li><li>liaise with approved subcontractor for any services diversion works</li></ul><p><strong>Job Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Diploma/Degree in Civil engineering/ Mechanical engineering and/or relevant field</li><li>Min 5 years’ experience in Utilities/ Rail projects.</li></ul><p><strong>Other Information:</strong><br /><strong>To apply, please include the following details inside your resume:</strong></p><ul><li>Reasons for leaving each past & current</li><li>employment</li><li>Salary drawn for each past & current employment</li><li>Expected Salary</li><li>Earliest availability date</li></ul><p><strong>How to apply</strong><br />Interested candidates who wish to apply for the position, you may send in your updated resume to <a href=\"mailto:search84@searchindex.com.sg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">search84@searchindex.com.sg</a><br /><strong>We regret that only short-listed candidates will be contacted shortly.</strong><br /><strong>Lionel Cheow</strong></p><p><strong>EA License | 14C7092</strong><br /><strong>EA Registration Number | R1105005</strong></p>",
